## Critical Issues

### 1. Scroll listener added with capture phase but removed without it — memory leak / stale handler

**File:** `client/src/components/SidebarOpinions/OpinionssPage.jsx`, lines 121–127
**Confidence:** 100

```js
document.addEventListener('scroll', scroll, true)   // capture phase
return () =>{
    document.removeEventListener('scroll', scroll)  // bubble phase — NOT the same listener
```

`addEventListener` and `removeEventListener` must receive identical arguments to match. Passing `true` (capture) on add but omitting it (defaults to `false`, bubble) on remove means the listener is **never removed**. Every mount creates a new leaked scroll listener. The `timeoutRef` clear at the end of the cleanup does not compensate for the orphaned listener.

