### 2. `throw` inside `catch` skips `finally` cleanup — dialog stays open after error

**File:** `client/src/components/SidebarOpinions/OpinionsEditor.jsx`, lines 42–49
**Confidence:** 95

```js
} catch (error) {
    setIsSaving(false)
    setOpinion('')
    throw new Error('error uploading data')   // re-throws…
} finally {
    setOpinion('')   // …so finally still runs, but…
    onClose();       // onClose() is called even on error
}
```

JavaScript's `finally` block **always** runs — even when `catch` re-throws. The actual bug here is the opposite of what was suspected: `onClose()` in `finally` executes unconditionally, so on a failed save the modal is dismissed and the user loses their typed opinion without any error message surfacing to them. The `throw` propagates to the caller, which is a React event handler — this becomes an unhandled promise rejection visible only in the console. The user experience is: button spins, modal closes, opinion gone, no visible error.

Fix — either surface the error to state instead of throwing, or at minimum only call `onClose()` on success:

```js
try {
    setIsSaving(true);
    await addOpinion(formdata, session?.access_token);
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['getOpinions'] });
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['getMyOpinions'] });
    setOpinion('');
    onClose();
} catch (error) {
    setError('Failed to post opinion. Please try again.');
} finally {
    setIsSaving(false);
}
```

