`undefined` is falsy, so:
- The guard `if(!isFetchinNextPage)` always passes — `fetchNextPage()` can be called while a fetch is already in flight, triggering duplicate requests.
- The loader `{isFetchinNextPage && <MoonLoader />}` never renders — users see no loading indicator while paginating.

The typo exists across two separate files and is used four times in `commentsCards.jsx` and four times in `UnreadNotificationCard.jsx`.

Note: `notificationsCards.jsx` destructures `isFetchingNextPage` correctly (line 150) — the bug is only in the other two files.

Fix: rename destructured variable to `isFetchingNextPage` in both files.

